  "text": "Project: MoSAIC-P38 Website.\nGoal: Build a Jekyll site using jekyll-theme-yat that replicates a specific reference image.\nKey Constraints:\n- Theme: jekyll-theme-yat\n- Font: Libre Franklin (Google Fonts)\n- Colors: LBNL Palette (Dark Blue #00313C, Teal #007681, Light Gray #B1B3B3, Dark Gray #63666A)\n- Structure: Logo Bar -> Teal Nav -> Hero (Title + 2 Images) -> Content.\n- Strategy: Approach 2 (Enhanced Blueprint). Prioritize maintainability, clear structure, and ease of modification.\n- Maintainability Plan:\n    - Centralized SCSS variables for branding.\n    - Modular HTML via Jekyll includes.\n    - Separation of design (SCSS) and structure (Markdown/HTML).\n    - Use of placeholders for assets to decouple design from final asset delivery.",
